The quantitative measures introduced in Sec.~\ref{haloparam} can now be computed. Figure~\ref{fig:Cr_Nhalo} shows the average number of nucleons participating in the potential halo region. Whereas $N_{\mathrm{halo}}$ is consistent with zero for \mbox{$N\le50$}, a sudden increase is seen beyond the \mbox{$N=50$} shell closure. The existence of a decorrelated region in the density of the last three Cr isotopes is consistent with the
